# deploy/managed-pulse.cron.example
#
# Phase 3a.3 cron schedule for the managed-trading dispatcher bridge.
#
# This file is an EXAMPLE. It is NOT auto-installed. To enable, copy
# the relevant lines into the operator's actual crontab (`crontab -e`)
# or systemd timer config. Verify a manual dry run first (see below)
# before adding to crontab.
#
# Why a separate file?
#   - The Primary-wallet pulse already runs at ~12:00 UTC. We schedule
#     managed-pulse 30 minutes later so they don't hit the Polymarket
#     CLOB simultaneously and we don't risk the managed-pulse bridge
#     reading half-written `recommendation.json` artifacts.
#
# Cadence: 1×/day at 12:30 UTC. Picked Pacific morning so the dogfood
# operator can review the per-user run-summary.md during US working
# hours.
#
# ## Required env (in `.env` or operator's shell profile)
#
#   DATABASE_URL=postgres://...                  # required
#   MANAGED_TRADING_MODE=paper                   # paper (default) or live
#   MANAGED_TRADING_USE_REAL_BALANCES=true       # paper-mode dogfood toggle
#   MANAGED_TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK=https://...    # optional Slack webhook
#   POLYMARKET_BUILDER_ADDRESS=0x...             # required in live mode
#   POLYMARKET_BUILDER_CODE=0x...                # required in live mode
#   POLYMARKET_BUILDER_API_KEY=...               # required in live mode
#   POLYMARKET_BUILDER_API_SECRET=...            # required in live mode
#   POLYMARKET_BUILDER_API_PASSPHRASE=...        # required in live mode
#   PRIVY_SESSION_SIGNER_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...       # required in live mode
#   POLYGON_RPC_URL=https://...                  # recommended (otherwise public RPC)
#
# ## How to enable
#
#   1. Make sure `pnpm pulse:recommend` runs as part of your existing
#      Primary pulse cron at 12:00 UTC and writes
#      `runtime-artifacts/pulse-live/<ts>-<runId>/recommendation.json`.
#      The managed-pulse bridge auto-discovers the most recent file —
#      no explicit handoff is needed.
#
#   2. Dry-run once manually (paper mode, real balances):
#
#         cd /path/to/forecasting-agent-poly
#         MANAGED_TRADING_USE_REAL_BALANCES=true pnpm managed:pulse --json | tee /tmp/managed-pulse-dry.json
#
#      Verify:
#         - exit code 0
#         - `/tmp/managed-pulse-dry.json` shows expected user count
#         - `runtime-artifacts/managed-pulse/<runBatchId>/run-summary.md`
#           lists every authorised user with status=completed (or a
#           reasonable skip reason like `empty_safe`)
#         - DB rows in `managed_paper_runs` + `managed_decisions` for
#           this batch
#
#   3. Append the line below into `crontab -e`. Substitute REPO_ROOT.
#      Logs both stdout (final JSON summary) and stderr (progress)
#      to a per-run cron.log inside the same archive directory.
#
#   4. Watch the first scheduled run. If anything looks wrong:
#         - SET `MANAGED_TRADING_MODE=paper` to disable live trading
#         - Comment out the cron line and re-test manually
#
# ## How to disable
#
#   Comment out the cron line below (prefix with `#`). Existing
#   `runtime-artifacts/managed-pulse/` archives are preserved.
#
# ## crontab line — uncomment + adjust paths to enable
#
# REPO_ROOT=/path/to/forecasting-agent-poly    # ← edit this
# 30 12 * * * cd "$REPO_ROOT" && /usr/bin/env -i HOME=$HOME PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin bash -lc 'pnpm managed:pulse --json' >> "$REPO_ROOT/runtime-artifacts/managed-pulse/cron.log" 2>&1
#
# ## systemd timer alternative
#
# If you prefer systemd over cron, drop these two units in
# `/etc/systemd/system/`:
#
#   /etc/systemd/system/managed-pulse.service
#   ----------------------------------------------------------
#   [Unit]
#   Description=Forecasting Agent Poly managed-pulse dispatcher
#   After=network-online.target
#
#   [Service]
#   Type=oneshot
#   WorkingDirectory=/path/to/forecasting-agent-poly
#   EnvironmentFile=/path/to/forecasting-agent-poly/.env
#   ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/pnpm managed:pulse --json
#   StandardOutput=append:/path/to/forecasting-agent-poly/runtime-artifacts/managed-pulse/cron.log
#   StandardError=append:/path/to/forecasting-agent-poly/runtime-artifacts/managed-pulse/cron.log
#   ----------------------------------------------------------
#
#   /etc/systemd/system/managed-pulse.timer
#   ----------------------------------------------------------
#   [Unit]
#   Description=Run Forecasting Agent Poly managed-pulse daily
#
#   [Timer]
#   OnCalendar=*-*-* 12:30:00 UTC
#   Persistent=true
#
#   [Install]
#   WantedBy=timers.target
#   ----------------------------------------------------------
#
#   sudo systemctl enable --now managed-pulse.timer
#
# ## Notes
#
#   - The bridge is idempotent within a single `runBatchId`; cron
#     re-runs always get a fresh batch (timestamp + uuid suffix).
#   - Failures fan out via `MANAGED_TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK` and are
#     persisted to the `risk_events` table for replay.
#   - To pause everything without removing the cron entry, set
#     `MANAGED_TRADING_PAUSED=true` (not yet wired — Phase 3b).
